{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.27",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 27 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:1",
      "text": "Job again took up his parable, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:2",
      "text": "“As God lives, who has taken away my right, the Almighty, who has made my soul bitter",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:3",
      "text": "(for the length of my life is still in me, and the spirit of God is in my nostrils);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:4",
      "text": "surely my lips will not speak unrighteousness, neither will my tongue utter deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:5",
      "text": "Far be it from me that I should justify you. Until I die I will not put away my integrity from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:6",
      "text": "I hold fast to my righteousness, and will not let it go. My heart will not reproach me so long as I live.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:7",
      "text": "“Let my enemy be as the wicked. Let him who rises up against me be as the unrighteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:8",
      "text": "For what is the hope of the godless, when he is cut off, when God takes away his life?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:9",
      "text": "Will God hear his cry when trouble comes on him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:10",
      "text": "Will he delight himself in the Almighty, and call on God at all times?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:11",
      "text": "I will teach you about the hand of God. I will not conceal that which is with the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:12",
      "text": "Behold, all of you have seen it yourselves; why then have you become altogether vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:13",
      "text": "“This is the portion of a wicked man with God, the heritage of oppressors, which they receive from the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:14",
      "text": "If his children are multiplied, it is for the sword. His offspring will not be satisfied with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:15",
      "text": "Those who remain of him will be buried in death. His widows will make no lamentation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:16",
      "text": "Though he heap up silver as the dust, and prepare clothing as the clay;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:17",
      "text": "he may prepare it, but the just will put it on, and the innocent will divide the silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:18",
      "text": "He builds his house as the moth, as a booth which the watchman makes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:19",
      "text": "He lies down rich, but he will not do so again. He opens his eyes, and he is not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:20",
      "text": "Terrors overtake him like waters. A storm steals him away in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:21",
      "text": "The east wind carries him away, and he departs. It sweeps him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:22",
      "text": "For it hurls at him, and does not spare, as he flees away from his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.27.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:23",
      "text": "Men will clap their hands at him, and will hiss him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
